I very much enjoyed this movie.  The story line was good, Mark Ruffalo was excellent, as always.  Adam Levine was a wonderful surprise.  I suppose he shouldn't have been as musicians do well at showing emotion.  For the little time that he was actually in the movie, he portrayed his role very well.  My only complaint is that I don't think Keira Knightley is a good enough singer to pull off the role.  She's eh, okay, but I would never buy a song she performed.  I think they could have gotten a stronger lead.
